{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1ef5ebc5-e1ef-42b2-924e-c1b5982134e7","content":"**Exit code 8** means \"no tests were discovered.\" Microsoft.Testing.Platform intentionally treats this as a failure by default (unlike VSTest which returned 0).\n\nThe fix is the added MSBuild property:\n\n```xml\n<TestingPlatformExitProcessOnMissingTests>false</TestingPlatformExitProcessOnMissingTests>\n```\n\nThis tells the test runner to return exit code **0** when zero tests are found, restoring the VSTest behavior. Since your `ConditionalTests.cs` is entirely behind `#if INCLUDE_SLOW_TESTS`, configurations that don't define that symbol will now pass CI again.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"22cf64f5-5b14-4bdd-af6e-238b620b2d6b","outputTokens":151,"requestId":"E3D0:1A0B9E:16657A2:190C856:6A052130"},"id":"041fc3f5-4310-4e34-8fb2-14f975ebb755","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:11:18.587Z","parentId":"e7477658-9812-40ab-8585-2f8078d137af"}
